      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's... that's a really dark way to look at it. But honestly, when I think about it, you're right. Every time I close my eyes, I just see the numbers and my dad's face. It's like there's this weight on my chest that won't go away. Everything I worked for is just... gone. It feels like the version of me that actually mattered died with the company. What am I even supposed to do with the rest of my life?",
